1. Uplašila sam se kada sam čula glasnu buku. (*uplašila* - past tense, 1st person singular) (I got scared when I heard a loud noise.)
2. Nisam se uplašila zmije u bašti jer znam da nije otrovnica. (*uplašila* - past tense, 1st person singular) (I didn't get scared of the snake in the garden because I know it's not venomous.)
3. Da li te je uplašila ta vest? (*uplašila* - past tense, 3rd person singular) (Did that news scare you?)
4. Uplašila bih se da vozim motor bez kacige. (*uplašila bih* - conditional tense, 1st person singular) (I would get scared if I rode a motorcycle without a helmet.)
5. Njegove reči su me uplašile. (*uplašile* - past tense, 3rd person plural) (His words scared me.)
6. Kada bih se uplašila, nikad ne bih skočila sa padobranom. (*uplašila - past tense, 1st person singular) (If I got scared, I would never jump with a parachute.)
7. Sestra se uplašila mraka i zato uvek drži upaljenu noćnu lampu. (*uplašila - past tense, 3rd person singular) (My sister is scared of the dark, that's why she always keeps a night lamp on.)
8. Da li te uplašilo što su se prozori jako tresli tokom oluje? (*uplašilo - past tense, 3rd person singular) (Did it scare you when the windows were shaking during the storm?)
9. Nikada se ne bih uplašila da sam sama u šumi noću. (*uplašila - past tense, 1st person singular) (I would never get scared if I were alone in the forest at night.)
10. Uplašila sam se kada sam videla pauka na zidu. (*uplašila - past tense, 1st person singular) (I got scared when I saw a spider on the wall.)